  "summary": "Binary columnar storage for TPC-H analytical workload. lineitem (60M) sorted by l_shipdate for zone map-based range filtering; orders (15M) sorted by o_orderdate. Low-cardinality columns (returnflag, linestatus, mktsegment, orderpriority, orderstatus) use dictionary encoding (uint8_t). Decimals stored as int64_t (cents×100). Dates as int32_t (days since epoch 1970) for fast range filtering. Block size 256K rows (~22MB per block) fits in L3 cache with overhead. Zone maps on shipdate/orderdate columns skip blocks during range predicates. Sorted indexes on join keys (orderkey, custkey, partkey, suppkey) enable probe-side lookups. Parallel ingestion via global thread pool (64 threads), permutation-based sorting for sorted tables, buffered binary writes."
